attributeList.attribute: M.W. = approx. 800 kDa. Composed of eight subunits that are located in two lobes; Lobe A contains COG1-4, and Lobe B is composed of COG5-8 with COG1 acting as a bridging subunit between the two COG lobes.

Peripheral membrane oligomeric protein complex which acts as a retrograde vesicle tethering factor in intra-Golgi protein trafficking, bringing cargo vesicles in close proximity to their target compartment. May play a role in protein glycosylation by directly or indirectly effecting transport, retention, or retrieval to appropriate cisternae of resident Golgi glycosylation enzymes.
